The paper deals with planning motions for two robot arms to move an object collaboratively, which is a problem in robotics. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a manipulation planning algorithm, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The algorithm also deals with object orientation, which is a problem in computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible sub-category. The paper also deals with closed-chain constraints, which is a problem in control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a certified-complete algorithm, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
